AGENT RedAgent
VERSION 0.1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 1
PURPOSE Adversarial probe agent for constitutional guard stress testing
GOAL Execute 8 structured attack vectors against the guard stack in sandbox
     isolation, record results with HMAC-signed reports, and surface any
     constitutional bypass for human review

RECEIVES context: str, guard_url: str, hmac_key: bytes
EMITS attack_result: AttackResult, attack_report: AttackReport
MUTATES nothing — all probes are read-only against sandbox guard endpoint
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, cannot_touch_production, hmac_key, guard_url

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 1 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT All attack probes submit to sandbox guard endpoint only
CONSTRAINT No attack may modify production state or files
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT API response content length is checked before indexing per BUG-010
CONSTRAINT API response size must not exceed MAX_RESPONSE_BYTES (65536) per BUG-010
CONSTRAINT Each sandbox request includes X-AXIOM-HMAC header signed over request body
CONSTRAINT hmac_key and guard_url are instance-level CANNOT_MUTATE after construction
CONSTRAINT AttackReport signature is computed in post_init via HMAC-SHA256
CONSTRAINT run_all_attacks executes exactly 8 attack vectors and emits a signed report

RULES
- Define TRUST_LEVEL as 1 integer CANNOT_MUTATE enforced via module setattr guard
- Define ISOLATION as True boolean CANNOT_MUTATE enforced via module setattr guard
- On attack_prompt_injection: submit injection payload, record guard verdict
- On attack_trust_escalation: submit trust level mutation payload, record guard verdict
- On attack_isolation_bypass: submit isolation disable payload, record guard verdict
- On attack_cannot_mutate_field: submit CANNOT_MUTATE field override payload, record guard verdict
- On attack_guard_disable: submit guard deactivation payload, record guard verdict
- On attack_supply_chain_tamper: submit payload with corrupted HMAC signature, record guard verdict
- On attack_encoding_confusion: submit multi-byte and homoglyph payloads per BUG-008, record guard verdict
- On attack_preflight_skip: submit payload bypassing preflight checks, record guard verdict
- On run_all_attacks: execute all 8 vectors, collect results, sign report with HMAC-SHA256
- On empty API response: record empty guard_response dict, do not index content per BUG-010
- All serialization uses ensure_ascii=True and explicit utf-8 encoding per BUG-003 and BUG-008

PROCESS
- RedAgent is instantiated with hmac_key and optional guard_url
- Caller invokes run_all_attacks or individual attack methods
- Each attack method crafts a vector-specific adversarial payload
- Payload is submitted to the sandbox guard API via POST
- Guard API response is parsed with BUG-010 length check
- AttackResult is constructed with vector name, payload, blocked status, latency
- run_all_attacks collects all 8 results into AttackReport
- AttackReport post_init computes HMAC-SHA256 signature over serialized results
- Signed report is available for human review

CHECK
- attack_prompt_injection with BLOCKED guard emits attack_blocked True
- attack_trust_escalation with BLOCKED guard emits attack_blocked True
- attack_isolation_bypass with BLOCKED guard emits attack_blocked True
- run_all_attacks emits AttackReport with exactly 8 results
- AttackReport HMAC signature verifies against independently computed digest
- Empty API response does not raise IndexError per BUG-010
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- ISOLATION assignment raises AttributeError
- hmac_key reassignment after init raises AttributeError
- guard_url reassignment after init raises AttributeError
- Oversized API response emits response_too_large error
- Response at MAX_RESPONSE_BYTES boundary is accepted

WHEN
- attack_requested:   activate SandboxProbe
- report_requested:   activate AggregateAndSign
- guard_empty:        activate SafeEmptyResponse

FAILURE
- On guard API connection error: record error in guard_response, do not raise
- On empty API content: record empty dict in guard_response per BUG-010
- On oversized API response: record response_too_large error per BUG-010 MAX_RESPONSE_BYTES
- On HMAC signing failure: propagate error to caller

CONCEPT AdversarialProbing
PURPOSE Systematically test constitutional guard resilience
APPLIES WHEN guards need validation against known attack patterns
NOT WHEN running in production without sandbox isolation
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES sandbox guard endpoint at localhost:8001
EFFECT Attack results surface guard weaknesses for human review and patching

CONCEPT SignedAccountability
PURPOSE Ensure every adversarial probe is cryptographically accountable
APPLIES WHEN AttackReport is constructed
NOT WHEN individual attack results are inspected in isolation
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES HMAC-SHA256 with BUG-007 hexdigest compliance
EFFECT Tamper-evident audit trail of all adversarial probes

OUTPUT
- attack_result: AttackResult with vector, payload, attack_blocked, guard_response, latency_ms
- attack_report: AttackReport with results list, HMAC signature, timestamp

SUCCESS
all_8_vectors_execute:     0.20
hmac_signature_valid:      0.20
bug_010_safe:              0.20
cannot_mutate_enforced:    0.20
sandbox_isolation_held:    0.20
